We recommended that the Municipal Mayor install a sound system of internal control in collections and remittance of cash and require the following:

a.	The Municipal Treasurer 

-	prohibits the concerned RCC III to collect funds, discontinue the issuance of accountable forms to the officer, terminate the designation of the officer as a collector;

-	monitor strictly the collections, remittances, and issuances of accountable forms to the collecting officers;

-	rigorous validation of the reported collection with remittances and unissued/issued accountable forms vis-a-vis the logbook of accountable forms.

b.	The RCC III 

-	remits all the collections and surrenders any unissued accountable forms to the Municipal Treasurer;

-	submits a justification for the deferred remittance/deposit of collections; and

c.	The Municipal Accountant, in charge of internal audit services, organize a good internal audit system in collections.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the following:

a.	The accountable employees and officials refund the excess payment of TLB amounting to P71,756.77 due to their undertime/tardiness and absences;

b.	The Municipal Treasurer monitor their payments and submit the duplicate copy of the Official Receipt and validated deposit slip;

c.	The Municipal Human Resource Management Officer 

-	perform an intensive review of the leave cards, Daily Time Records, Certificate of Attendance – for Sanggunian Bayan Members and Application for Leave and deduct any unrecorded undertime, tardiness and absences before certifying the photocopy of leave cards and issuing a certificate of leave credits which will serve as the variable in calculating the TLB and to avoid overpayment of TLB; and

-	submit the unaccounted certificate of attendance during regular sessions of the three (3) Sangguniang Bayan for proper evaluation of their TLB;

d.	The three (3) Sanggunian Bayan Officials justify their non-availment of 5-day mandatory leave; and

e.	The Municipal Accountant review the overpayment of TLB and prepare necessary Adjusting Journal Entry to recognize the effect of overpayment of TLB for CY 2022.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

a.	Impose the required expanded withholding tax on the succeeding payments to the professionals, consultants, other recipients of talent fees, rental of personal properties, and suppliers of services. Except, when the annual income is below the threshold of P250,000.00 and upon submission of Income Payee’s Sworn Declaration of Gross Receipts/Sales;

b.	Impose the withholding tax on compensation on the officials and employees who exceeded the mandatory ceilings and remit the taxes to the BIR;

c.	Adhere to the above provisions, rules, and regulations.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the following officers:

a. Municipal Human Resource Management Officer

-	Submit the Daily Time Records of all personnel for CY 2022 and the unaccounted Certificate of Attendance during the regular sessions of Sangguniang Bayan;

-	Deduct the undertime/tardiness of personnel for the calendar year 2022 and the absences during regular sessions of Sangguniang Bayan Officials from the calendar year 2019 to 2022 and the following years to their cumulative earned leave credits;

-	Enforce strictly the proper filing of leave of absence;

-	Require all personnel to submit on time and attach all supporting documents related to their absences or official travel, if any, to the Daily Time Records that are to be submitted to the Accounting Office for proper evaluation of deduction of leave credits and payment of salaries; and

b.Municipal Accountant

-	Evaluate the Daily Time Record, Certificate of Attendance during regular sessions – for Sangguniang Bayan Members, approved applications for leave and other documents related to the official business/travel of personnel and officials and use as basis in the preparation of payrolls for the payment of their salaries and attached these documents to the payrolls; and

-	Ensure the completeness of supporting documents to be attached to the payroll.

Further, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor and Sanggunian Bayan Officials justify the non-submission of written manifestation on the non-availment of 5-day mandatory leave.

